## Overview
The package contains the following files:
- Dataset
	- hepth.mat : HepTh dataset
- evaluation : MAP evaluation (codes from Ben Hamner (ben@benhamner.com))
- RWER
	- calRWER.m : compute RWER using the iterative method
	- Normalize.m : normalize an adjacency matrix
- SuRe 
	- SuRe.m : learn the restart vector
	- caldrdc.m : compute dr/dc using the iterative method
	- calr_tilde.m : calculate r_tilde (sum(M(y,:) - M(x,:)) in the paper) using GMRES
	- logistic.m : logistic function (loss function)
	- deriv_logistic.m : derivative of the logistic function

## Usage
Extract the zip file and move the extracted folder.
Then, you should add pathes into MATLAB environment. Please type the following command in MATLAB:

	addPath

We also provide a demo file for our method SuRe. Please type the following command to run the demo:

	demo



